ADO EKITI – The secretary of the former and serving ex-officio members of the People’s Democratic Party(PDP) Hon Hellen Taiwo-Adebakin has congratulated Hon Bisi Kolawole on his emergence as the party’s standard-bearer for June 18 Governorship poll. Hon Adebakin in her congratulatory message also commended the PDP Stakeholders in Ekiti and at the National for ensuring peaceful conflict of the Governorship primaries in Ekiti. The PDP chieftain also urged Kolawole’s co-contestants to display the spirit of sportsmanship by embracing Kolawole’s candidacy and work for the party’s victory in the all-important poll. Office Vandalism: Look Inward For Perpetrators, Gombe APC Tells… Oyo PDP Commiserates With Folarin Over Wife’s Death According to her, Kolawole is a, loyal and committed party man with a good track record. She said ” I have been monitoring the happenings in Ekiti State as it concerns our party,(PDP) particularly, the peaceful and transparent nature the Governorship primaries was conducted. From available records, Kolawole has been a loyal and committed party man. He has laboured for the party, even in trying times and he has never left the party for once. ” So,I am not surprised today that the PDP has decided to forward his selfless service for the party by making him the standard-bearer. He was a member of the Ekiti State House of Assembly, Commissioner and later State Chairman. By any standard, he is an entrenched member of our party. And I believe in his ability  and capacity to return PDP to power  in Ekiti ” Adebakin however thanked former governor Ayo Fayose and other PDP stakeholders for making it happen in a peaceful atmosphere.